15. Amaltheo: the villa of At· ticus near Buthrotum, in Epirus, was so called from the nymph Amalthea. The library of this villa was adorned with the busts of noted Romans. Cicero's was among the rest. Beneath the busts (Nepos, Att. 18. 5) were com· memorative inscriptions.
